<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFBCFFE6FF1CFE744BA2FC2B" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FF1CFE744B34FDEB" blockId="13.[113,764,417,986]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FF1CFE74498AFE48" box="[151,232,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FE3CFE744BF3FE4B" author="BURMAN" box="[439,657,417,442]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="230" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 230)</bibRefCitation>
cited two illustrations (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FF76FE1448F5FE2B" author="BURMAN" box="[253,407,450,474]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref8920" refString="BURMAN, J. (1737). Thesaurus Zeylanicus, exhibens plantas in insula Zeylana nascentes. Amsterdam." title="Thesaurus Zeylanicus, exhibens plantas in insula Zeylana nascentes" type="book" year="1737">BURMAN, 1737</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 87; 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FE64FE144BFEFE28" author="PLUKENET" box="[495,668,449,473]" firstAuthor="PLUKENET" journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref10088" refString="PLUKENET, L. (1705). Amaltheum botanicum. London." title="Amaltheum botanicum" type="book" year="1705">PLUKENET, 1705</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 407, fig. 2) and a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FF77FE344859FE08" box="[252,315,482,505]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Pryon</emphasis>
collection from 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFBCFFE6FE64FE344B7FFE08" box="[495,541,482,505]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Java</collectingRegion>
. The latter, extant in G-PREL, is designated here as the 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBCFFE6FE66FDD44B33FDEB" box="[493,593,514,538]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBCFFE6FF1CFDF44BA2FC2B" blockId="13.[113,764,417,986]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FF1CFDF44897FDC8" author="FRASER-JENKINS, C. R. &amp; K. N. GANDHI &amp; B. S. KHOLIA &amp; A. BENNIAMIN" box="[151,501,545,570]" journalOrPublisher="Dehra Dun" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref9270" refString="FRASER-JENKINS, C. R., K. N. GANDHI, B. S. KHOLIA &amp; A. BENNIAMIN (2017). An Annotated Checklist of Indian Pteridophytes 1: Lycopodiaceae to Thelypteridaceae. Dehra Dun." title="An Annotated Checklist of Indian Pteridophytes 1: Lycopodiaceae to Thelypteridaceae" type="book" year="2017">FRASER-JENKINS et al. (2017: 286)</bibRefCitation>
designated as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBCFFE6FD00FDF44B88FDCB" box="[651,746,546,570]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">lectotype</typeStatus>
a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FFFAFD944996FDA8" box="[113,244,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Pieter Hertog</emphasis>
collection from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBCFFE6FE17FD94488AFDAB" box="[412,488,578,602]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
(G-PREL [G00360109]), annotated by C.V. Morton as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBCFFE6FE3CFDB44B7AFD8B" box="[439,536,610,634]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">holotype</typeStatus>
. It was cited by Burman’s father (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FE8FFD5448C2FD6B" author="BURMAN" box="[260,416,642,666]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref8920" refString="BURMAN, J. (1737). Thesaurus Zeylanicus, exhibens plantas in insula Zeylana nascentes. Amsterdam." title="Thesaurus Zeylanicus, exhibens plantas in insula Zeylana nascentes" type="book" year="1737">BURMAN, 1737</bibRefCitation>
) in the 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FE7EFD544BAEFD6B" box="[501,716,642,666]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Thesaurus Zeylanicus</emphasis>
and is the basis for plate 
<quantity id="16109B71FFBCFFE6FED9FD7448E4FD4B" box="[338,390,674,698]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2098" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" unit="in" value="87.0">87 in</quantity>
the same work, precisely the plate mentioned by Burman in the 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FE3DFD144B57FD2B" box="[438,565,706,730]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Flora Indica</emphasis>
. Unfortunately, as 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FFFAFD3449A2FD08" box="[113,192,738,761]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Hertog’s</emphasis>
specimen was not cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FE50FD344BD3FD0B" author="BURMAN" box="[475,689,737,762]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="230" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 230)</bibRefCitation>
, unlike 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FFFAFCD449DBFCE8" box="[113,185,770,793]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Pryon’s</emphasis>
(see above), this lectotypification cannot be accepted (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FFF0FCF44803FCCB" author="TURLAND" box="[123,353,802,826]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="TURLAND" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref10318" refString="TURLAND, N. J., J. H. WIERSEMA, F. R. BARRIE, W. GREUTER, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, P. S. HERENDEEN, S. KNAPP, W. - H. KUSBER, D. - Z. LI, K. MARHOLD, T. W. MAY, J. MCNEILL, A. M. MONRO, J. PRADO, M. J. PRICE &amp; G. F. SMITH (2018). International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Veg. 159." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="proceedings" year="2018">TURLAND et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 9.12). 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FE55FCF44BA7FCC8" author="DAS" box="[478,709,801,826]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="DAS" journalOrPublisher="Indian J. Forest." page="286" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" pagination="285 - 286" part="41" refId="ref9136" refString="DAS, P., P. M. PADHYE &amp; S. GUPTA (2018). Second-step lectotypification of Pteris ensiformis Burm. f. (Pteridaceae). Indian J. Forest. 41: 285 - 286." title="Second-step lectotypification of Pteris ensiformis Burm. f. (Pteridaceae)" type="journal article" year="2018">DAS et al. (2018: 286)</bibRefCitation>
provided a superfluous second-step lectotypification based on the same specimen, apparently overlooking that 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBCFFE6FDC2FCB44846FC68" author="FRASER-JENKINS, C. R. &amp; K. N. GANDHI &amp; B. S. KHOLIA &amp; A. BENNIAMIN" journalOrPublisher="Dehra Dun" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" refId="ref9270" refString="FRASER-JENKINS, C. R., K. N. GANDHI, B. S. KHOLIA &amp; A. BENNIAMIN (2017). An Annotated Checklist of Indian Pteridophytes 1: Lycopodiaceae to Thelypteridaceae. Dehra Dun." title="An Annotated Checklist of Indian Pteridophytes 1: Lycopodiaceae to Thelypteridaceae" type="book" year="2017">FRASER-JENKINS et al. (2017: 286)</bibRefCitation>
already unambiguously designated a single specimen (“[...] 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBCFFE6FE97FC744B69FC4B" box="[284,523,930,954]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zeylanicum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBCFFE6FE97FC744B69FC4B" box="[284,523,930,954]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Polypodium zeylanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
etc. Herbier Delessert collection Burman, 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBCFFE6FEC8FC1448D4FC2B" box="[323,438,962,986]" pageId="13" pageNumber="106">Holotypus</typeStatus>
, det. C.V. Morton [...]”).
</paragraph>
